###
# ============================================================
# IPR MANAGEMENT SYSTEM - COMPLETE API TEST FILE
# Spring Boot · Java 21 · PostgreSQL · Port 8081
# ============================================================
# INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Run steps top-to-bottom on first setup (seed order matters)
# 2. After Step 1  (Authority Login)  → update @authorityToken below
# 3. After Step 9  (HOD Login)        → update @hodToken below
# 4. After Step 10 (Employee Login)   → update @employeeToken below
# 5. Replace @id variables with actual IDs returned from responses
# ============================================================
# END-TO-END WORKFLOW SUMMARY:
# [0] Seed authority user in DB → Login → get @authorityToken
# [1] Authority creates: Department → Office → Employee(s) → User credentials
# [2] HOD logs in → opens filing window (notification)
# [3] Employee logs in → creates IPR Return → adds properties → adds declaration → submits
# [4] HOD reviews → approves or returns with remarks
# [5] If returned → Employee corrects → resubmits
# [6] HOD approves → Authority sees final approved return
# ============================================================


@baseUrl        = http://localhost:8081/api/v1
@authorityToken = PASTE_AUTHORITY_TOKEN
@hodToken       = PASTE_HOD_TOKEN_HERE
@employeeToken  = PASTE_EMPLOYEE_TOKEN_HERE

# ── Common IDs (fill after creation) ─────────────────────────
@departmentId   = 1
@officeId       = 1
@employeeId     = 1
@hodEmployeeId  = 2
@iprReturnId    = 1
@propertyId     = 1
@declarationId  = 1
@notificationId = 1


# ============================================================
# AUTH - LOGIN (public, no token required)
# ============================================================

### [PUBLIC] Step 1 - Seed Authority user in DB first, then login
# Run this SQL once before testing:
# INSERT INTO users (id, username, password, role, employee_id)
# VALUES (nextval('user_sequence'), 'authority', 'authority@123', 'ROLE_AUTHORITY', null);
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "authority",
  "password": "authority@123"
}

### → Expected: { "token": "eyJ...", "role": "ROLE_AUTHORITY", ... }
# → Copy token → paste into @ authorityToken above

### [PUBLIC] Step 2 - HOD Login (after credentials created in Step 7)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "hod_finance",
  "password": "hod@123"
}

### → Copy token → paste into @hodToken above

### [PUBLIC] Step 3 - Employee Login (after credentials created in Step 7.1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "emp_rajan",
  "password": "emp@123"
}

### → Copy token → paste into @employeeToken above


# ============================================================
# AUTHORITY - DEPARTMENT MANAGEMENT (Authority token required)
# ============================================================

### [AUTHORITY] Step 4 - Create Department
POST {{baseUrl}}/authority/department/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "name": "Finance Department"
}

### → Note returned id → set @departmentId

### [AUTHORITY] Step 4.1 - Create another Department
POST {{baseUrl}}/authority/department/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "name": "Public Works Department"
}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 4.2 - Get All Departments
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/department/get
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 4.3 - Get Department By Id
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/department/get/{{departmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 4.4 - Update Department
PUT {{baseUrl}}/authority/department/update/{{departmentId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "name": "Finance & Accounts Department"
}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 4.5 - Delete Department (cascades to offices, employees, users, returns)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/authority/department/delete/{{departmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}
### (Commented out — run manually when needed)

# ============================================================
# AUTHORITY - OFFICE MANAGEMENT (Authority token required)
# ============================================================

### [AUTHORITY] Step 5 - Create Office (under Finance Department)
POST {{baseUrl}}/authority/office/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "name": "Accounts Branch - Agartala",
  "departmentId": {{departmentId}}
}

### → Note returned id → set @officeId

### [AUTHORITY] Step 5.1 - Create another Office (same department)
POST {{baseUrl}}/authority/office/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "name": "Treasury Office - Agartala",
  "departmentId": {{departmentId}}
}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 5.2 - Get All Offices
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/office/get
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 5.3 - Get Office By Id
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/office/get/{{officeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 5.4 - Get Offices By Department
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/office/get/department/{{departmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 5.5 - Update Office
PUT {{baseUrl}}/authority/office/update/{{officeId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "name": "Accounts Branch - Agartala (Updated)",
  "departmentId": {{departmentId}}
}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 5.6 - Delete Office (cascades to employees, returns)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/authority/office/delete/{{officeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}


# ============================================================
# AUTHORITY - EMPLOYEE MANAGEMENT (Authority token required)
# ============================================================

### [AUTHORITY] Step 6 - Create Employee (regular)
POST {{baseUrl}}/authority/employee/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "name": "Rajan Kumar Das",
  "email": "rajan.das@tripura.gov.in",
  "service": "Tripura Civil Service",
  "lengthOfService": "8 years",
  "presentPostHeld": "Assistant Accounts Officer",
  "placeOfPosting": "Agartala",
  "officeId": {{officeId}}
}

### → Note returned id → set @employeeId

### [AUTHORITY] Step 6.1 - Create Employee (will become HOD)
POST {{baseUrl}}/authority/employee/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "name": "Priyanka Majumdar",
  "email": "priyanka.majumdar@tripura.gov.in",
  "service": "Tripura Civil Service",
  "lengthOfService": "15 years",
  "presentPostHeld": "Deputy Director Finance",
  "placeOfPosting": "Agartala",
  "officeId": {{officeId}}
}

### → Note returned id → set @hodEmployeeId

### [AUTHORITY] Step 6.2 - Get All Employees
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/employee/get
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 6.3 - Get Employee By Id
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/employee/get/{{employeeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 6.4 - Update Employee
PUT {{baseUrl}}/authority/employee/update/{{employeeId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "name": "Rajan Kumar Das",
  "email": "rajan.das@tripura.gov.in",
  "service": "Tripura Civil Service",
  "lengthOfService": "9 years",
  "presentPostHeld": "Senior Accounts Officer",
  "placeOfPosting": "Agartala",
  "officeId": {{officeId}}
}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 6.5 - Delete Employee (cascades to user credentials and all IPR returns)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/authority/employee/delete/{{employeeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}


# ============================================================
# AUTHORITY - USER CREDENTIAL MANAGEMENT (Authority token required)
# ============================================================

### [AUTHORITY] Step 7 - Create HOD credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/authority/user/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "username": "hod_finance",
  "password": "hod@123",
  "role": "ROLE_HOD",
  "employeeId": {{hodEmployeeId}}
}

### Valid roles: ROLE_EMPLOYEE, ROLE_HOD, ROLE_AUTHORITY

### [AUTHORITY] Step 7.1 - Create Employee credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/authority/user/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "username": "emp_rajan",
  "password": "emp@123",
  "role": "ROLE_EMPLOYEE",
  "employeeId": {{employeeId}}
}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 7.2 - Get All Users
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/user/get
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 7.3 - Delete User credentials (employee record stays, removes login access)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/authority/user/delete/{{employeeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}


# ============================================================
# AUTHORITY - VIEW & MANAGE ALL IPR RETURNS (system-wide)
# ============================================================

### [AUTHORITY] Step 8 - Get All IPR Returns (all roles, all departments)
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/ipr-return/get
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 8.1 - Get HOD Pending Returns (submitted by HOD, pending AUTHORITY approval)
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/ipr-return/hod/pending
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 8.2 - Approve HOD's IPR Return
PUT {{baseUrl}}/authority/ipr-return/approve/{{iprReturnId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "remarks": "Verified and approved by Authority"
}

### [AUTHORITY] Step 8.3 - Return HOD's IPR Return (mandatory remarks)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/authority/ipr-return/return/{{iprReturnId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "remarks": "Declaration date is incorrect. Please correct and resubmit."
}


### ============================================================
# HOD - FILING WINDOW / NOTIFICATIONS (HOD token required)
# ============================================================
# Login as HOD first (Step 2), then run these.

### [HOD] Step 9 - Open Filing Window for an Office (create notification)
POST {{baseUrl}}/hod/notification/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "session": "2025-2026",
  "message": "Annual IPR return filing is now open for 2025-2026. All employees must submit by the deadline.",
  "officeId": {{officeId}},
  "startDate": "2026-07-01",
  "endDate": "2026-08-14",
  "active": true
}

# Rules: endDate - startDate must be <= 45 days
# Only one active notification per office at a time
# → Note returned id → set @notificationId

### [HOD] Step 9.1 - Get All Notifications (HOD's department only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/hod/notification/get
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

### [HOD] Step 9.2 - Get Notifications By Office
GET {{baseUrl}}/hod/notification/get/office/{{officeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

### [HOD] Step 9.3 - Get Active Notification for an Office
GET {{baseUrl}}/hod/notification/get/active/{{officeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

# Returns 404 if no active notification for that office

### [HOD] Step 9.4 - Extend Filing Window (only end date can be extended, not reduced)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/hod/notification/update/{{notificationId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "session": "2025-2026",
  "message": "Filing window extended by 2 weeks due to technical issues.",
  "officeId": {{officeId}},
  "startDate": "2026-07-01",
  "endDate": "2026-08-28",
  "active": true
}

# Rules: new endDate cannot be before current endDate
# Total window (from original startDate) cannot exceed 60 days

### [HOD] Step 9.5 - Deactivate Notification (close filing window early)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/hod/notification/update/{{notificationId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "session": "2025-2026",
  "message": "Filing window closed.",
  "officeId": {{officeId}},
  "startDate": "2026-07-01",
  "endDate": "2026-08-14",
  "active": false
}

### [HOD] Step 9.6 - Delete Notification
# DELETE {{baseUrl}}/hod/notification/delete/{{notificationId}}
# Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}


# ============================================================
# HOD - VIEW & MANAGE EMPLOYEE IPR RETURNS (HOD token required)
# ============================================================

### [HOD] Step 10 - Get All Employee Returns in HOD's Department
GET {{baseUrl}}/hod/ipr-return/get
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

# Returns only ROLE_EMPLOYEE returns within HOD's department

### [HOD] Step 10.1 - Get Pending (Submitted) Returns
GET {{baseUrl}}/hod/ipr-return/pending
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

# Returns only SUBMITTED returns for HOD's department employees

### [HOD] Step 10.2 - Get IPR Return By Id
GET {{baseUrl}}/hod/ipr-return/get/{{iprReturnId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

# Returns 400 if return belongs to a different department

### [HOD] Step 10.3 - Approve Employee's IPR Return
PUT {{baseUrl}}/hod/ipr-return/approve/{{iprReturnId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "remarks": "Return verified. All properties declared correctly."
}

# Remarks are optional for approve
# Return must be in SUBMITTED status

### [HOD] Step 10.4 - Return Employee's IPR Return (mandatory remarks)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/hod/ipr-return/return/{{iprReturnId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "remarks": "Property at Krishnanagar not declared properly. Please add acquisition mode and correct the present value."
}

# Remarks are MANDATORY for return action
# Return must be in SUBMITTED status

### [HOD] Step 10.5 - Get Workflow Log for an IPR Return
GET {{baseUrl}}/hod/workflow-log/get/ipr/{{iprReturnId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

# Returns all actions: CREATED, SUBMITTED, RETURNED, APPROVED

### [HOD] Step 10.6 - Get Employees in HOD's Department
GET {{baseUrl}}/hod/employee/get
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}


# ============================================================
# EMPLOYEE - PROFILE (Employee token required)
# ============================================================
# Login as Employee first (Step 3), then run these.

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 11 - Get My Profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/employee/me
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

# Returns: id, name, email, service, lengthOfService,
#          presentPostHeld, placeOfPosting, officeId,
#          officeName, departmentId, departmentName


# ============================================================
# EMPLOYEE - IPR RETURN (core filing workflow)
# ============================================================

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 12 - Check if Filing Window is Open for my Office
GET {{baseUrl}}/employee/notification/get/active/{{officeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

# Returns active notification details if window is open
# Returns 404 if no active notification for that office

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 13 - Create IPR Return (DRAFT) — requires open filing window
POST {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

{
  "reportingYear": "2025-2026",
  "asOnDate": "2026-07-31",
  "totalAnnualIncome": 720000.00,
  "isNoProperty": false
}

# isNoProperty: true  → skip adding properties, can submit directly
# isNoProperty: false → must add at least one property before submit
# → Note returned iprId → set @iprReturnId

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 13.1 - Create IPR Return with No Property declaration
POST {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

{
  "reportingYear": "2024-2025",
  "asOnDate": "2025-07-31",
  "totalAnnualIncome": 650000.00,
  "isNoProperty": true
}

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 13.2 - Get My IPR Returns (all)
GET {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/get
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 13.3 - Get IPR Return By Id
GET {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/get/{{iprReturnId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 13.4 - Update IPR Return (only DRAFT or RETURNED status)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/update/{{iprReturnId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

{
  "reportingYear": "2025-2026",
  "asOnDate": "2026-07-31",
  "totalAnnualIncome": 750000.00,
  "isNoProperty": false
}

# 400 error if status is SUBMITTED or APPROVED

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 13.5 - Submit IPR Return (DRAFT or RETURNED → SUBMITTED)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/submit/{{iprReturnId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

# 400 if isNoProperty=false and no properties added yet
# 400 if filing window is closed

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 13.6 - Delete IPR Return (only DRAFT status)
# DELETE {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/delete/{{iprReturnId}}
# Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}
# 400 if status is not DRAFT


# ============================================================
# EMPLOYEE - PROPERTY MANAGEMENT (Employee token required)
# ============================================================

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 14 - Add Property to IPR Return (self-owned)
POST {{baseUrl}}/employee/property/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

{
  "iprReturnId": {{iprReturnId}},
  "locationAddress": "Plot No. 12, Krishnanagar, Agartala, Tripura - 799001",
  "propertyType": "Residential House",
  "propertyDescription": "Double storey RCC building, 1200 sq ft",
  "acquisitionCost": 2500000.00,
  "acquisitionYear": "2019",
  "presentValue": 3200000.00,
  "ownerName": "Rajan Kumar Das",
  "ownerRelation": "SELF",
  "acquisitionMode": "Purchase",
  "acquisitionDetails": "Purchased from private party. Registered at Sub-Registrar office, Agartala.",
  "annualIncome": 0.00,
  "remarks": "Self-occupied residential house"
}

# ownerRelation: SELF / SPOUSE / DEPENDENT
# acquisitionMode: Purchase / Inheritance / Gift / Lease / Mortgage / Other
# → Note returned id → set @propertyId

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 14.1 - Add Property owned by Spouse
POST {{baseUrl}}/employee/property/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

{
  "iprReturnId": {{iprReturnId}},
  "locationAddress": "Agricultural Land, Mohanpur, West Tripura",
  "propertyType": "Agricultural Land",
  "propertyDescription": "2 bigha agricultural land, cultivated",
  "acquisitionCost": 800000.00,
  "acquisitionYear": "2015",
  "presentValue": 1500000.00,
  "ownerName": "Sunita Das",
  "ownerRelation": "SPOUSE",
  "acquisitionMode": "Inheritance",
  "acquisitionDetails": "Inherited from father-in-law. Mutation done in 2016.",
  "annualIncome": 45000.00,
  "remarks": "Income from paddy cultivation"
}

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 14.2 - Get Properties for an IPR Return
GET {{baseUrl}}/employee/property/get/ipr/{{iprReturnId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 14.3 - Update Property
PUT {{baseUrl}}/employee/property/update/{{propertyId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

{
  "iprReturnId": {{iprReturnId}},
  "locationAddress": "Plot No. 12, Krishnanagar, Agartala, Tripura - 799001",
  "propertyType": "Residential House",
  "propertyDescription": "Double storey RCC building, 1200 sq ft, self-occupied",
  "acquisitionCost": 2500000.00,
  "acquisitionYear": "2019",
  "presentValue": 3500000.00,
  "ownerName": "Rajan Kumar Das",
  "ownerRelation": "SELF",
  "acquisitionMode": "Purchase",
  "acquisitionDetails": "Purchased from private party via bank loan.",
  "annualIncome": 0.00,
  "remarks": "Self-occupied. Bank loan fully repaid."
}

# 400 error if return is in SUBMITTED or APPROVED status

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 14.4 - Delete Property
# DELETE {{baseUrl}}/employee/property/delete/{{propertyId}}
# Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}
# 400 error if return is in SUBMITTED or APPROVED status


# ============================================================
# EMPLOYEE - DECLARATION (Employee token required)
# ============================================================

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 15 - Add Declaration (sign the IPR return)
POST {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-declaration/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

{
  "iprReturnId": {{iprReturnId}},
  "declarationText": "I hereby declare that the return enclosed namely, Form - VI are complete, true and correct to the best of my knowledge and belief in respect of information due to be furnished by me under the provision of Rule-18 of the Tripura Civil Services (Conduct) Rules, 1988.",
  "agreed": true,
  "declarationDate": "2026-07-31",
  "place": "Agartala",
  "employeeSignature": "Rajan Kumar Das"
}

# Only one declaration per IPR return (409 if already exists)
# → Note returned id → set @declarationId

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 15.1 - Get Declaration for an IPR Return
GET {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-declaration/get/ipr/{{iprReturnId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 15.2 - Update Declaration
PUT {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-declaration/update/{{declarationId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

{
  "iprReturnId": {{iprReturnId}},
  "declarationText": "I hereby declare that the return enclosed namely, Form - VI are complete, true and correct to the best of my knowledge and belief in respect of information due to be furnished by me under the provision of Rule-18 of the Tripura Civil Services (Conduct) Rules, 1988.",
  "agreed": true,
  "declarationDate": "2026-07-31",
  "place": "Agartala",
  "employeeSignature": "Rajan Kumar Das"
}

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 15.3 - Delete Declaration
# DELETE {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-declaration/delete/{{declarationId}}
# Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}


# ============================================================
# EMPLOYEE - WORKFLOW LOG (Employee token required)
# ============================================================

### [EMPLOYEE] Step 16 - Get Workflow History of my IPR Return
GET {{baseUrl}}/employee/workflow-log/get/ipr/{{iprReturnId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

# Returns all actions in chronological order:
# CREATED → SUBMITTED → RETURNED → SUBMITTED → APPROVED
# Each log has: action, actionByUserId, role, remarks, actionDate


# ============================================================
# HOD - FILING THEIR OWN IPR RETURN (HOD token, employee endpoints)
# ============================================================
# HOD uses the same /employee endpoints as a regular employee.
# Key difference: the filing window check is SKIPPED for ROLE_HOD.

### [HOD] Step 17 - HOD creates their own IPR Return (no window check)
POST {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "reportingYear": "2025-2026",
  "asOnDate": "2026-07-31",
  "totalAnnualIncome": 1200000.00,
  "isNoProperty": false
}

### [HOD] Step 17.1 - HOD adds property to their own return
POST {{baseUrl}}/employee/property/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "iprReturnId": {{iprReturnId}},
  "locationAddress": "House No. 45, Battala, Agartala, Tripura",
  "propertyType": "Residential House",
  "propertyDescription": "Three bedroom apartment, 1800 sq ft",
  "acquisitionCost": 4500000.00,
  "acquisitionYear": "2017",
  "presentValue": 6000000.00,
  "ownerName": "Priyanka Majumdar",
  "ownerRelation": "SELF",
  "acquisitionMode": "Purchase",
  "acquisitionDetails": "Purchased through SBI home loan. Loan closed in 2024.",
  "annualIncome": 0.00,
  "remarks": "Self-occupied"
}

### [HOD] Step 17.2 - HOD adds declaration to their return
POST {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-declaration/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "iprReturnId": {{iprReturnId}},
  "declarationText": "I hereby declare that the return enclosed namely, Form - VI are complete, true and correct to the best of my knowledge and belief in respect of information due to be furnished by me under the provision of Rule-18 of the Tripura Civil Services (Conduct) Rules, 1988.",
  "agreed": true,
  "declarationDate": "2026-07-31",
  "place": "Agartala",
  "employeeSignature": "Priyanka Majumdar"
}

### [HOD] Step 17.3 - HOD submits their return (goes to AUTHORITY for approval)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/submit/{{iprReturnId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}


# ============================================================
# ERROR / EDGE CASE TESTS
# ============================================================

### [TEST] Step 18 - Login with wrong password → 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "emp_rajan",
  "password": "wrong_password"
}

### [TEST] Step 18.1 - Access AUTHORITY endpoint with EMPLOYEE token → 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/authority/employee/get
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### [TEST] Step 18.2 - Access HOD endpoint with EMPLOYEE token → 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/hod/ipr-return/get
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### [TEST] Step 18.3 - Create IPR Return without open filing window → 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

{
  "reportingYear": "2030-2031",
  "asOnDate": "2031-07-31",
  "totalAnnualIncome": 800000.00,
  "isNoProperty": false
}

### [TEST] Step 18.4 - Submit IPR Return without any properties (isNoProperty=false) → 400
PUT {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/submit/{{iprReturnId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

# Use an iprId that has isNoProperty=false and zero properties added

### [TEST] Step 18.5 - Duplicate IPR Return for same reporting year → 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/employee/ipr-return/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

{
  "reportingYear": "2025-2026",
  "asOnDate": "2026-07-31",
  "totalAnnualIncome": 720000.00,
  "isNoProperty": false
}

# Expected: "You have already filed an IPR return for 2025-2026"

### [TEST] Step 18.6 - Duplicate username → 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/authority/user/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authorityToken}}

{
  "username": "emp_rajan",
  "password": "another@123",
  "role": "ROLE_EMPLOYEE",
  "employeeId": {{employeeId}}
}

### [TEST] Step 18.7 - Create notification exceeding 45 days → 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/hod/notification/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "session": "2025-2026",
  "message": "Test window",
  "officeId": {{officeId}},
  "startDate": "2026-07-01",
  "endDate": "2026-09-30",
  "active": true
}

# endDate - startDate = 91 days, exceeds 45-day limit → 400

### [TEST] Step 18.8 - Approve IPR that is not in SUBMITTED status → 400
PUT {{baseUrl}}/hod/ipr-return/approve/{{iprReturnId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "remarks": "Approved"
}

# Use an iprId that is in DRAFT status

### [TEST] Step 18.9 - Return IPR without remarks → 400
PUT {{baseUrl}}/hod/ipr-return/return/{{iprReturnId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{hodToken}}

{
  "remarks": ""
}

# Empty remarks for return action → 400

